"Schulze R.E., Kunz R.P.","Potential shifts in optimum growth areas of selected commercial tree species and subtropical crops in southern Africa due to global warming",1995,"Journal of Biogeography","22","4-5",,"679","688",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0029513057&partnerID=40&md5=d106b31de9da466cbb80a95a3bada64c","Dept Agric Eng, Univ of Natal, Pietermaritzburg, Scottsville, South Africa","Schulze, R.E., Dept Agric Eng, Univ of Natal, Pietermaritzburg, Scottsville, South Africa; Kunz, R.P., Dept Agric Eng, Univ of Natal, Pietermaritzburg, Scottsville, South Africa","Possible impacts of a future temperature increase on the spatial distributions of optimum growth areas is species dependent, favouring Eucalyptus grandis, avocado Persea americana and pecan nut Carya sp., but not Pinus patula. According to the climatic threshold model used, the timber species and horticultural crops considered produced a westward shift to ""new' climatically suitable areas in the future. -from Authors",,"avocado; global warming; optimum growth area; pecan nut; Africa, (Southern); Carya; Carya illinoinensis; Eucalyptus; Eucalyptus grandis; Persea americana; Pinus patula",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"English",,,Scopus,2-s2.0-0029513057
